    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Octoflat Theme]]></title>
    <link href="http://alexgaribay.github.io/blog/2013/04/28/octoflat-theme/"/>
    <updated>2013-04-28T12:11:00-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://alexgaribay.github.io/blog/2013/04/28/octoflat-theme</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2>Beginnings</h2>

<p>I have created my first Octopress theme today called Octoflat. The theme is inspired by flat design. It uses <a href="" title="http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/">Twitter Bootstrap</a> and Designmodo&#8217;s <a href="" title="https://github.com/designmodo/Flat-UI">Flat UI</a>. All the colors chosen are the colors listed on Flat-UI&#8217;s demo page.</p>

<h2>Installing the theme</h2>

<h4>As a submodule</h4>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cd your_octopress_dir
</span><span class='line'>git submodule add https://github.com/alexgaribay/octoflat .themes/octoflat
</span><span class='line'>rake install['octoflat']
</span><span class='line'>rake generate</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h4>Grabbing the latest updates as a module</h4>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cd your_octopress_dir
</span><span class='line'>git submodule update</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h4>As a clone</h4>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cd your_octopress_dir
</span><span class='line'>git clone https://github.com/alexgaribay/octoflat .themes/octoflat
</span><span class='line'>rake install['octoflat']
</span><span class='line'>rake generate</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h4>Calling for Help</h4>

<p>I need help making the theme more customizable to the end user. So any help in doing so would be greatly appreciated.</p>
]]></content>
